### Remote client-side stress test via vmauth (IntelliJ HTTP Client)
###
### 1) Generate 1k Prometheus-text metrics payload (client-style):
###    python tests/generators/biz_date_input_generator.py \
###      --job "producer_a" \
###      --last-days 30 \
###      --metric-count 1000 \
###      --metric-prefix "vmj_stress_metric" \
###      --output tmp/vmauth_prometheus_text_1k.txt
###
### 2) Set params below for your target vmauth endpoint/token.
### 3) Send request to push the full block through vmauth -> vmagent -> sidecar.

@remoteVmUrl = https://your-vmauth-host
@token = replace_me
@jobName = producer_a

### Optional read probe through vmauth (adjust selector if needed)
GET {{remoteVmUrl}}/api/v1/query?query=count({job="{{jobName}}"})
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Write 1k metrics (Prometheus text format with biz_date labels) through vmauth
POST {{remoteVmUrl}}/api/v1/import/prometheus
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: text/plain

< ../tmp/vmauth_prometheus_text_1k.txt
